b'       INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY MADRAS Academic Section  Circular No.4D/JN2016/B2/2016 &nbsp;&nbs;p; &nb;sp; &nb;sp; Dated 25.08.2016   Dear Students / Scholars,  Sub:  Production of Identity Cards during Quizzes and Examinations E2 Reg. </span  QuizI  for the B.Tech./Dual Degree/M.Tech./MBA/M.Sc. /M.A. / MS  and Ph.D students/scholars commences on  &nb;sp; Thursday the  1 st  September 2016 .      All students should carry with them their Identity Cards to the Quizzes/ Examinations. They should produce their identity card to the Invigilator. If, for any reason, they are not able to produce the Identity Cards at the time of examination, the Head of the Department/Invigilator may permit them to write the examination, with the condition that they should produce the Identity Card to the Head of the Department/ Invigilator(s) within one hour after the closure of the examination. In case some students do not possess or have lost their Identity Cards, they are required to meet the Librarian immediately, and get new identity card made, against the payment of  Rs .500/.  In the case of any correction to be made, fresh card will be issued on payment of Rs.250/. <span styleD"fontfamily:"Book Antiqua",serif" langD"ENUS"Sd/ <span styleD"fontfamily:"Book Antiqua",serif" langD"ENUS"Deputy Registrar (Courses)  To All students  throE2 students@list.iitm.ac.in  Copy to : 1. All Heads of Departments  throE2 email 2. The Dean, Students  throE2 email 3. The Librarian, Central Library  throE2 email 4. All faculty throE2 faculty@list.iitm.ac.in</span  '

